Good 👍 — this is the most important part after applying IDMS, ITMS, and CatalogSource.
I’ll give you the exact next steps in correct order so your upgrade doesn’t fail.


---

✅ After Applying (IDMS + ITMS + CatalogSource)

🧭 Step 1: Wait for cluster to pick mirror config

oc get co

👉 Ensure:

All ClusterOperators → Available=True

No progressing/Degraded issues



---

🔍 Step 2: Verify image pull is using your registry

Run:

oc get pods -A -o wide | grep -i image

Or better:

oc adm release info <your-local-release-image>

Example:

oc adm release info bastion.srib-lab-ocp.lan:8443/ocp4/openshift4:4.19.23-x86_64

👉 If this works → mirror is correct ✅
👉 If error → mirror config issue ❌


---

📦 Step 3: Verify CatalogSource is READY

oc get catalogsource -n openshift-marketplace

👉 Check:

STATUS = READY


Then:

oc get pods -n openshift-marketplace

👉 Catalog pod should be:

Running ✅



---

🔌 Step 4: Check Operators (very important)

oc get packagemanifests

👉 You should see operators listed

If empty ❌ → CatalogSource issue


---

🧪 Step 5: Test image pull manually (optional but powerful)

oc debug node/<node-name>

Then inside:

crictl pull bastion.srib-lab-ocp.lan:8443/ocp4/openshift4:<tag>

👉 Confirms nodes can pull images


---

🚀 Step 6: Set Upgrade Image

Now prepare upgrade:

oc adm upgrade

👉 Should show available updates (if channel configured)


---

If not showing (offline case 👇)

You must upgrade using image:

oc adm upgrade \
  --to-image=bastion.srib-lab-ocp.lan:8443/ocp4/openshift4:4.19.23-x86_64 \
  --allow-explicit-upgrade


---

📊 Step 7: Monitor Upgrade

oc get clusterversion

and:

watch oc get co


---

🚨 Common Problems After This Step

Issue	Cause

Image pull error	IDMS/ITMS wrong
No operators visible	CatalogSource issue
Upgrade not starting	Wrong release image
Degraded operators	Missing images



---

🏁 Final Flow Summary

👉 After applying mirror configs:

1. Wait for cluster stable


2. Verify release image


3. Verify catalog source


4. Check operators


5. Trigger upgrade


6. Monitor




---

💡 Pro Tip (Don’t Skip)

Run this before upgrade:

oc adm upgrade --allow-explicit-upgrade --to-image=<image> --dry-run

👉 This avoids breaking cluster 👍


